social_posts.post_text: National treasure

Happy birthday to my amazing husband Henry which is also a great excuse to post this since the only other thing I want to talk about is the @barbie movie. Henry is not on Instagram but he really is the best. 😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍😍

Now that NYE has passed and we are in to January I wanted to remind everyone that this is also Stalking Awareness Month. Since I’m so public with my case I wanted to let everyone know I’m always happy to talk to anyone and hopefully offer some advice or resources. Stalking while complicated and nuanced, is a widely misunderstood and dangerous silent epidemic. @followuslegally always has great info so make sure to give them a follow. I’ll be doing podcasts, IG lives, and panels all month including a special event here in LA that will be announced soon.

@titanicexhibit photo dump. The photo ops were fun but it was the personal stories that really resonated with me. Lots of people creating fake identities to start a new life and secret forbidden romances which apparently inspired the film. 💙 💎

Thank you @newsnationnow  @nancyloo for having @drkrismohandie and I on to discuss the stalking component to the Idaho tragedy. While there was so much I wish we had gotten into like the fact 58% of stalking starts when the victim is under 25, this incredibly painful story is a reminder how serious this crime is and why we need more education and prevention. I don’t know how many horrible things have to happen before people start listening to survivors. @followuslegally @stopstalkingusnow @evawintl #stalking #stalkingawareness

It’s been 2 years since the @ladaoffice asked me to join @losangelescvab to serve as an advocate for stalking/gender based violence. I’m incredibly proud that within the last year we were able to connect the office to @followuslegally who provided critical training for the dedicated reps from the Bureau of Victims Services. This event is another awesome opportunity for education and platforming survivor stories and needs. #stalkingawarenessmonth #stalking #losangeles

Lately I’ve been working on some projects that are truly incredible but to call them intense would be an understatement. To balance this we decided to go to NYC for a few days to get stupid, eat vegan dim sum, and see something beautiful which I will post tomorrow. Hope you’re all well and finding time to squeeze in as much fun as you can. Thank you @museumofsex we had the best day!

Amazing early Valentine’s Day trip with Henry to see the @manfredthierrymugler exhibit at @brooklynmuseum Mugler is my all time favorite designer so seeing all 108 pieces I’ve obsessed over since I was a teen was pretty incredible. The video for Too Funky literally changed my life so taking in all that beauty was such a special experience. #mugler #muglerized
Thank you @ladaoffice for bringing me on to the @losangelescvab and providing a platform to advocate for fellow survivors.

I don’t get to talk about a lot of the work I do out of respect and privacy for the survivors but I thought this was cool and wanted to share. It was also great connecting with so many amazing activists and advocates.
We lost Nomi very suddenly this morning. She was my soul mate animal and such a special little creature. I’m completely devastated but forever grateful for the life we had together.

Thank you @dannybeckart for surprising me with this beautiful oil painting tribute of my girl Nomi. I’ll forever be broken hearted by her absence but this depiction of her in my favorite designer @manfredthierrymugler captures her personality and taps into so many amazing memories. Thank you for this kind and thoughtful gift I will treasure forever. #minpin #minpinstagram
I’m looking forward to participating in this @missrepresentation series with @carolineheldman I hope you can join us for this important discussion.

I’m still really mourning Nomi hard and I’m sure I always will but Hollywood has been helping mend our hearts. She’s a runty little min pin at only 6lbs but she has the cutest quirks like making these “meep” sounds and loves smelling makeup. Nomi thought the sidewalk was her runway and had a huge personality that I miss terribly, but had zero interest in most dogs. Hollywood however is trying to be the mayor of Dogtown and thinks they are all her new best friend she hasn’t met yet. Even though their loss is so painful I’m forever grateful for dogs and all that they give us. I still can’t believe someone abandoned little Hollywood at a groomer but thank you @littlekabukisgrooming and @theglitterwhorelife for bringing us together. 1st 📷 by @itstroyjensen #minpin #minpinstagram

I loved everything about @barbiethemovie and seeing how much joy @barbie brings everyone. With that being said, I have so much respect for what the @wgawest and @sagaftra are doing with the strike. I hope they get everything they want and deserve. These artists create magic that helps us get through dark times and should be treated properly. I only wish those of us toiling away in unscripted could do the same but we have no union and we are all really struggling with this merger madness right now too. Seeing @barbiethemovie yesterday with a bunch of awesome women was really what I needed. Thank you @marielodiandreakos for organizing and always being the best. #barbie #barbiecollector #barbiecore #barbiethemovie

What a sweet man and what an incredible life. For all the magic he brought to my childhood I still think my favorite memory of him is a story he told @djhenryselfesq and I from his childhood. I will never do it justice in retelling it but it had us crying with laughter. I will always treasure the random phone calls and could never get offended when he had to get off the phone because David Hasselhoff was calling. Paul was the first person to introduce me to the wonder that is Brookledge and where I knew we had to get married. I literally still pay for extended mail forwarding because I couldn’t bare the thought of missing one of his Christmas cards. He once told me he kept like a dossier on all his friends of the day they met, likes and dislikes, etc. Truly one of a kind.  One of my all time favorite projects that never got to make it to completion was back in my curating days. I had pitched Paul on an idea for an art show I had called Pee-wee’s Whitehouse which played with the concept of Pee-wee running for President. Paul liked it enough to get me a meeting with his management and we had a lot of fun tossing around ideas. One of my favorites was for a campaign speech including one red bicycle for every American. Paul also wanted to make everyone fill out impossibly long surveys while they waited in line William Castle style and kept asking me about lasers like they have in museums around priceless objects. I don’t know if I can share any of the concept art for legal reasons but I will just say one of my all time favorite artists made something amazing and you all would be screaming if you knew how cool it could have been. I guess that speaks to how awesome he was when even something that I failed to take across the finish line still gives me such joy to think about.
I’ve got a lot of other things in the works but I can share this one for now.

I’m in a new TMZ series about celebrity stalking cases. While the 13.5+ million Americans currently being stalked are obviously not all celebrities, I’m appreciative anytime I’m given a platform to advocate for all the other victims/survivors. Especially since we are the most at risk and the least protected. Makeup @itstroyjensen hair @hisvintagetouch PR @itstherealdara

Quick life update. I’ve been working as an Investigator and training to become a licensed PI at a really awesome firm specializing in stalking cases and missing persons. I’m about to start the FBI Citizens Academy which is exciting for a bunch of reasons. I will be continuing to advocate for victims/survivors as part of the @ladaoffice Crime Victims Advisory Board and was recently awarded some commendations from the city and office. I had a health scare and was hospitalized for 3 days so I’m doing my best to be honest about the toll this kind of work can do on our health and finding some balance in life. I’ve also been having a lot of fun raising Hollywood who is still very much a crazy puppy, but she’s so smart and affectionate it’s worth all the stolen socks and 4am zoomies. Hope you’re all doing well and staying safe. 🕵️‍♀️ 🐕

After being hospitalized again (autoimmune disorders are fun) I managed to get discharged just in time to make it to my FBI Citizens Academy class and the incredible John Waters @academymuseum preview ✨Thank you @marielodiandreakos ✨ I don’t even know where to begin about how important John Waters has been to me since my teens but I will say the show is amazing and they did a beautiful job of honoring his weird and wonderful career. Since John is the Pope of Trash I made sure to wear my @moschino 🗑️ purse and @normakamali 🐆 dress for the occasion.

My health is still not awesome, but there was no way @djhenryselfesq and I were missing the incredible @keithharingfoundation show at @thebroadmuseum If you’re in LA and haven’t gone don’t sleep on this one. #keithharing

I guess everyone really *IS* thinking about the Roman Empire. @djhenryselfesq and I started the weekend with a screening of the new uncut & remixed version of Caligula with @malcolm_mcdowell and ended with a fun party at @kendallegetty and @jrocket88 house. Everyone looked so beautiful I wish I took more photos. Hope you all had a nice weekend too. Dress by @normakamali

Hollywood photo dump. This adorable little fun sized chocolate is obsessed with my scrunchies which is all well and fine until I’m sleeping and she realizes that’s what’s holding up my ponytail. This is my third min pin but my first puppy. Puppies are WILD. 🍫 🐕 #minpin #puppy

I love that I’ve lived in LA my whole life and I’m still discovering awesome historic gems. We celebrated the equally amazing @marielodiandreakos birthday at a beautiful tea house in Pasadena which formerly housed a secret lab for Albert Einstein.

After 8 days in the hospital with more questions than answers, I decided to try the @prenuvo full body scan. Thank you @djhenryselfesq for the awesome anniversary gift. Excited to get my results in 5 days. #prenuvo #prenuvoscan

I can’t believe FBI LA Citizens Academy graduation is this Tuesday. It’s been an incredible experience learning from all the Special Agents and being able to be a liaison to the community. Today we were invited to participate in a range day and observe a SWAT exercise. Having zero firearms experience it was a little intimidating at first (especially the shotgun) but I did my best with our awesome instructors. As someone who literally grew up reading @johndouglasmindhunter this has been such a special opportunity. I’m excited to go to Quantico and continue my education with all these wonderful people. #fbi #fbicitizensacademy
@jeffreymichaelanderson has been my friend for 18 years and this is our only photo together.
I can’t wait to go to Quantico!

Tokyo photo dump #4
Hachiko statue
Tokyo Disneyland

One of Japan’s unofficial landmarks, the Hachiko statue in Shibuya is a homage to the faithful Akita dog who waited at Shibuya Station every day for his master, even after his death. Today, it’s one of the most popular meeting places in Tokyo.

The Story of Hachiko
Professor Eizaburo Ueno of Tokyo University adopted Hachiko in Akita prefecture in the early 1920s. The two were inseparable, with Hachiko accompanying his master to Shibuya Station each day when the professor would head off to work at Tokyo’s Imperial University. The faithful pup would come back to the station each afternoon at 3pm to greet Ueno upon his return. Unfortunately, the professor died in 1925 while at the university and never returned for a final goodbye with his pet. However, the loyal Hachiko continued to visit the station daily until his own death nearly 10 years later. His own death made headlines, and he was cremated and buried next to his beloved owner.

Everyone said we would be crazy not to go to DisneySea because it’s their most beautiful park so that’s how we spent our last full day. They weren’t wrong, it’s stunning. #disneysea

I’m not ready to come home today. Tokyo has been incredible. I’ve never felt so safe and happy in my life. I won’t even take public transportation in LA because I’ve had so many bad experiences but everything is different here. I’m so grateful for this trip and only wish I came out sooner.
Just landed in Oahu with my husband and his family so I had to throw on this @normakamali I hope everyone gets to close out this year with the people and things they love 🌺
Wholesome Hawaiian Disney holiday with my husband and his sweet family. How the hell is it almost 2024? 🌺

Since so much of my life is spent between activism and entertainment, January is pretty bonkers with National Stalking Awareness Month and Emmy events. There is something HUGE coming up advocacy wise but tonight since I’m a member of the @televisionacad it was great to celebrate my TV peers. Here’s to an amazing 2024 for everyone!

This is the big news I’ve been dancing around. Myself and a group of other amazing survivor activists have been invited to speak at the White House for listening session and events around the 20th anniversary of National Stalking Awareness month. So much to say. So much work to do. Obviously this is an incredibly painful subject but our stories are so heartbreaking and now we are all really being heard.
